I’m back in DC for a few days and am suddenly feeling motivated to create and share content on Life is Foodieful again! I guess this city is my muse…?

My work team and I had the most wonderful time yesterday at @immigrantfood’s Aperitivo Hour. From their website:

Aperitivo: a drink/light meal that takes place at the end of the workday as a warm-up to dinner.

The menu is limited to a few small bites, and we sampled them all! My highlights were the tequeños, hummus, and shishito peppers. The wings were also a huge hit at the table!

For drinks, I had the Amalfi Spritzer from the aperitivo hour menu, and my colleagues chose Old Fashioneds from the extensive and creative Old Fashioned menu!

We peeped the dinner and brunch menus, and they looked incredible. Might have to make another visit before we head back to Boston on Monday!

It’s not easy to eat fresh, healthy meals during a kitchen reno, but I’m getting by with a little help from @aerofarms! #ad

AeroFarms microgreens are now available NATIONWIDE in Whole Foods, so I’m able to get my hands on them whenever I want! I’ve been putting them on my takeout, my heat n’ eat meals, and eating them straight from the package. I’ve found it’s a great way to add flavor and nutrition to my meals while my kitchen is under construction!

A few of you have told me that you’ve tried AeroFarms based on my recommendation, which I love to hear!! Let me know in the comments - have you seen AeroFarms out in the wild? If you tried them, what did you think?

Who loves a one pot pasta moment? If you do, there’s a great recipe for you in the @aerofarms cookbook! #ad

This simple, easy recipe calls for their tender, peppery baby arugula, but I used the micro spicy mix - and garnished with micro arugula - because I saw it featured in my local @wholefoods and thought it would add a great kick to the recipe. (Spoiler alert: I was right!)

You can find the “official” recipe - and tons of other great pasta, salad, soup, taco, and smoothie recipes - on the AeroFarms website, but here’s how I did it:

Ingredients:

- 1 package of @aerofarms micro spicy mix
- 1 handful of @aerofarms micro arugula
- 1 box of protein penne (I used Barilla)
- 28 oz can diced tomatoes (including juice)
- 2 cups mushroom broth
- 5 cloves minced garlic
- 1.5 tsp dried oregano
- 1/4 cup chopped fresh basil
- 2 tbsp olive oil
- 1 tsp salt
- a few shakes crushed red pepper

Instructions:

1) in a large pot, add all ingredients except the fresh greens. If the pasta isn’t completely covered with liquid, add more mushroom broth. Once contents have come to a boil, cook until pasta is al dente, stirring often.

2) Once pasta is al dente, remove from heat and fold in the micro spicy mix and basil. Let it stand covered for 5-10 min.

3) Serve into bowls and top with the micro arugula.

Don’t forget to tag me and @aerofarms if you make this recipe!

A little baby update for y’all: in the last couple weeks, she’s JUST started to sleep through the night. But she’s still waking up at about 6am every morning. So my coffee intake is still… high 😆.

So I was THRILLED when @atlascoffeeclub offered to send me some beans! Their subscription allows you to try  exotic, fair trade coffee that you won’t find anywhere else. I loved the Brazil, which has tasting notes of coconut, chocolate, and a hint of vanilla.

With code ARIELLE50ATLAS, you can get 50% off your first bag! (Full disclosure: if you use my code, I’ll get a kickback. It’s a win-win!)

My parents took me to try @rancholewis a couple weeks ago when I was down for a visit in Charleston, and it was fantastic! If you’re down there, I highly recommend you give this spot - owned by the people behind @lewisbarbecuechs - a try!

My veggie enchiladas were perfect - fresh, flavorful, and not overpowered by cheese.

My mom said her shrimp fajitas were the best she’s ever had!

And my dad ordered a whole rack of ribs for himself. Lawl.

It’s #blackfoodfridays AND #earthday… so there couldn’t be a more perfect day to feature @theotherplate ! This Black, woman-owned business makes some of the yummiest plant-based, grain-free cookies I’ve had.

I stumbled upon Sabrina’s booth last weekend in Charleston, and had to stop when I saw her sign! We ended up having a lovely chat, and she told me all about the cool things she’s doing in Charleston, Atlanta, and LA.

Not in one of those cities? Not to worry! Free shipping is available when you order from the website (theotherplate.com).

Last week we treated ourselves to a very special lunch at @thecapitalgrille for Dany’s bday. He wanted a great steak, and that’s what he got… but I DIDNT get a photo 😆.

I had the tuna steak, which was incredible. We also shared the lobster bisque, which was brimming with huge chunks of lobster meat. The service was great, as you’d expect at a place like this 😊.

The complimentary bday desserts were the literal icing on the cake! (Or I guess if we’re being literal, they were… the literal cake? 😂)
